US-08 — Social Media Share Dropdown (Reporting Page Update)

Overview

For this update, I added a subtle social media sharing feature for admin users on the Reporting page.

The goal was to allow admins to post report insights directly to multiple platforms (Website, Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn) without cluttering the page with a large card. Instead of a full-size card, the feature now appears as a small “Share ▾” button in the existing Download toolbar.

This feature works entirely on the frontend and preserves all existing functionality. No backend routes or external libraries were added in this update.


---------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Frontend Integration — Share Dropdown Button
---------------------------------------------------------------------

I added a “Share ▾” button inside the existing Download toolbar.

File: src/app/reporting/page.js

The button appears next to the export buttons (PDF, CSV, XLSX, HTML) and the existing “Create Shareable Link” button. It only renders for admin users and when reportData exists.

This ensures the dropdown is:

- Subtle and less visually dominant
- Accessible without adding a new card
- Functional only when a report is loaded

Behavior breakdown:

| Condition | Result |
|-----------|--------|
| UserRole !== 'admin' | Button does not render |
| reportData is null | Button does not render |
| reportData exists & user is admin | Button appears in toolbar |
| Button clicked | Dropdown panel toggles open/close |
| Platforms selected | Admin can select multiple platforms |
| Post button clicked | handlePostToSocialMedia() runs |

Updated toolbar layout now looks like:

Download Toolbar (PDF / CSV / XLSX / HTML / Create Shareable Link / Share ▾)


---------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Dropdown Menu & Platform Selection Logic
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Inside ReportingPage, I added the following state and logic:

- `selectedPlatforms` — tracks platforms chosen for sharing
- `showSocialMenu` — toggles visibility of the dropdown
- `uploadStatus` — displays success/failure of posting
- `isUploading` — prevents multiple clicks during posting

The dropdown shows a compact panel containing:

- Checkboxes for each platform (Website, Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn)
- A small “Post” button to trigger posting
- Status text to show upload results

Function flow:

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Admin clicks “Share ▾” to open dropdown |
| 2 | Admin selects one or more platforms |
| 3 | Admin clicks “Post” |
| 4 | handlePostToSocialMedia() simulates upload (or triggers API) |
| 5 | uploadStatus updates success/failure message |
| 6 | Dropdown remains open for additional selections |

The checkbox selection allows multiple platforms to be chosen simultaneously. Posting is asynchronous with basic error handling.


---------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Why Dropdown Approach Was Used
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Instead of a large card, a dropdown was chosen to:

- Reduce visual clutter
- Integrate directly with the existing Download toolbar
- Keep the feature subtle for admins
- Avoid changing page layout or adding extra containers

This design maintains a clean UI and ensures that the social sharing feature does not distract non-admin users.


